WSJ900406-0156
</DOCNO>
<DOCID>
900406-0156.
</DOCID>
<HL>
   Tesoro Petroleum Wins Verdict
</HL>
<DATE>
04/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4
</SO>
<CO>
   CGP TSO
</CO>
<LP>
   SAN ANTONIO, Texas -- Tesoro Petroleum Corp. said it won a
$6.4 million verdict against a foreign subsidiary of Coastal
Corp.
   The company said a New York Supreme Court jury found that
Holborn Oil Co., a Bermuda-based unit of Coastal, had agreed
to purchase 25,000 metric tons of gasoline from Tesoro in May
1979, before a steep decline in the world petroleum market.
Holborn later denied entering into the contract and refused
to accept delivery of the gasoline, Tesoro said, forcing
Tesoro to sell the gasoline at a loss. The jury verdict
represented Tesoro's loss and accrued interest.
</LP>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>
WSJ900406-0155
</DOCNO>
<DOCID>
900406-0155.
</DOCID>
<HL>
   International:
   Lufthansa to Join Venture
   To Expand Soviet Airport
   ----
   Special to The Wall Street Journal
</HL>
<DATE>
04/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A16
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP FREST G.LHA G.AEG G.SZG DRSDY
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   FRANKFURT -- Deutsche Lufthansa AG said it will join four
West German companies to invest 750 million marks ($441.3
million) in a 50-50 joint venture it has formed with
Aeroflot, the Soviet national airline, to update and expand
the Moscow airport, Sheremetjevo I.
   West Germany's national air carrier, which is 51%
government owned, announced a year earlier that it had signed
a letter of intent for the project. Feasibility studies were
made during the past 11 months.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Sheremetjevo I airport in Moscow, as well as other
Soviet airports in the future, will be modernized, expanded
and operated by the joint venture. The 750 million marks will
be used to expand and update a passenger terminal in Moscow,
to build an international freight terminal, to build a
waiting hall and to build an airport hotel.
   In addition to Lufthansa, partners in the venture will
include electronics concern AEG AG, Flughafen Frankfurt am
Main, Salzgitter subsidiary Noell G.m.b.H and Dresdner Bank
AG.
   Lufthansa also said it received a comprehensive
maintenance contract to service the fleet of Airbus planes
owned by Aeroflot. Lufthansa didn't disclose financial
details of its new Aeroflot service contract.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
