<HL>
   Campbell Soup Facility Closing
</HL>
<DATE>
04/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3
</SO>
<CO>
   CPB
</CO>
<LP>
   CAMDEN, N.J. -- Campbell Soup Co. said it will close its
Chicago warehouse Sept. 28 as part of a consolidation of
distribution facilities in the Midwest.
   Following the facility's closing, the company will
distribute its products to midwestern customers by using
plants in Napoleon, Ohio, and Paris, Texas.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company hasn't yet negotiated severance benefits for
the Chicago facility's 70 union employees affected by the
closing.
