<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
</IN>
<LP>
   WIESBADEN, West Germany -- The production of raw steel in
West Germany slipped 5.2% to 9.8 million metric tons in the
first quarter from the like period of 1989, the Federal
Statistics Office said.
   Output of raw iron was down 6.9% to 7.8 million tons in
the first three months of this year from a year earlier, the
statistics office added.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In March alone, raw-steel output fell 0.9% to 3.5 million
tons, while iron output was off 3.4% from a year earlier to
2.7 million tons, the agency said.
