   WASHINGTON -- The Senate confirmed the nominations of
Philip Jackson and Robert Larson to be members of the
Oversight Board of the Resolution Trust Corp.
   The approvals, which came on voice votes, complete the
five-member body. The board sets policy and supervises the
work of the RTC, the agency created to sell or merge sick
savings and loans.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Larson is chief executive officer of Taubman Co., a
Bloomfield, Mich., real-estate development company. Mr.
Jackson is an adjunct professor at Birmingham Southern
College in Alabama and a former banking executive.
   The other members of the board are Treasury Secretary
Nicholas Brady, Housing and Urban Development Secretary Jack
Kemp, and Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan.
