agreement recently signed between Ericsson and Mexican
Telephone with a total value of six billion kronor.
   Further orders are also expected for power and
transmission equipment as well as for other specific projects
over the five-year period, Ericsson said.
   It said the order was a result of the Mexican government's
determination to expand the country's telecommunications
system.
