<HL>
   Business Brief -- Mitsui Taiyo Kobe Bank Ltd.:
   J. Dickson Brown Agrees
   To Form a Joint Venture
</HL>
<DATE>
04/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8
</SO>
<CO>
   J.MUB J.TBB
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Mitsui Taiyo Kobe Bank Ltd. and J. Dickson Brown Inc. of
the U.S. agreed to form a joint venture in option and swap
instruments, an official at the Japanese bank said.
   The new firm will make markets in interest-rate swaps and
in a variety of options focusing on interest rates, according
to the official. The new firm is expected to begin operation
this autumn.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mitsui Taiyo Kobe will hold 66.6% of the venture, with the
rest held by J. Dickson Brown. The new firm, which will be be
capitalized at $2.3 million, will be based in New York with
representative offices in London and Tokyo, the bank official
said.
